{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d84a1a35-8c19-4b9d-b026-7dc1d08700c1","content":"Use the `--filter` option with a fully qualified class name filter:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nOr using the `ClassName` trait:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter ClassName~ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\". If you need an exact match and know the full namespace, use `=`:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName=YourNamespace.ReportExporterTests\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"832273c3-c68e-43e3-88a0-500dab48a7aa","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to run only the `ReportExporterTests` class using `dotnet test`. This is a straightforward question about the dotnet test CLI filter syntax.","outputTokens":185,"requestId":"E3EA:321F09:5AC756:686B2A:6A0524A1"},"id":"e599cb40-e8cb-4960-9584-0eabd317efcd","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:25:58.768Z","parentId":"ed160976-48ea-42d9-af9b-c7f58a7c8cf9"}
